$k_stmts[] = "INSERT INTO ".K_TBL_DATA_TEXT." (page_id, field_id, value, search_value) VALUES (48, 81, '<p>\\r\\n	Afshin founded Mojo Mobility in 2005 sensing a need for a ubiquitous, intuitive method to charge and power the expanding range of mobile devices. He has been leading Mojo and has been instrumental in the growth and building of the company. Before founding Mojo Mobility, Afshin was president of Exel Technologies which focused on providing strategic and investment management advice to companies and governments. The Government of Republic of Ireland was a major client where Exel Technologies managed an investment and grant portfolio of 150M Euros and over 50 IT Hardware projects for Science Foundation Ireland and associated Institutes. Prior to that, Afshin led Product Management and Product Development at Digilens Corp. where he had overall responsibility for the definition, design and development of the company&rsquo;s products until its acquisition by Hoya Corp. Prior to that, Afshin held a number of roles at Lucent Technologies including managing Strategy and Business Development at Lucent&rsquo;s Broadband Networks Business Unit. In the earlier part of his career, Afshin held a number of product development and R&amp;D roles with AT&amp;T Bell Laboratories, Hughes Electronics &amp; NASA (JPL).</p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n	Afshin holds an MBA from Columbia University, a Ph.D. and M.S. in Electrical Engineering from Univ. of Southern CA and Bachelors of Engineering and Physics Degrees from University of Redlands. Afshin is the inventor on 45 issued and pending patents and has authored 66 papers in refereed technical journals, books, and conferences.</p>\\r\\n', 'Afshin founded Mojo Mobility in 2005 sensing a need for a ubiquitous, intuitive method to charge and power the expanding range of mobile devices. He has been leading Mojo and has been instrumental in the growth and building of the company. Before founding Mojo Mobility, Afshin was president of Exel Technologies which focused on providing strategic and investment management advice to companies and governments. The Government of Republic of Ireland was a major client where Exel Technologies managed an investment and grant portfolio of 150M Euros and over 50 IT Hardware projects for Science Foundation Ireland and associated Institutes. Prior to that, Afshin led Product Management and Product Development at Digilens Corp. where he had overall responsibility for the definition, design and development of the companys products until its acquisition by Hoya Corp. Prior to that, Afshin held a number of roles at Lucent Technologies including managing Strategy and Business Development at Lucents Broadband Networks Business Unit. In the earlier part of his career, Afshin held a number of product development and R&amp;D roles with AT&amp;T Bell Laboratories, Hughes Electronics &amp; NASA (JPL). Afshin holds an MBA from Columbia University, a Ph.D. and M.S. in Electrical Engineering from Univ. of Southern CA and Bachelors of Engineering and Physics Degrees from University of Redlands. Afshin is the inventor on 45 issued and pending patents and has authored 66 papers in refereed technical journals, books, and conferences.');";
