$k_stmts[] = "INSERT INTO ".K_TBL_FULLTEXT." (page_id, title, content) VALUES (74, 'Electrical Engineer', 'MOJO_EE Electrical Engineer This is an opportunity for an experienced electrical engineer who brings innovative electrical engineering and embedded system expertise to help the engineering team with various design, testing, and product development activities of the company. The technology includes power supply / magnetics design, battery charger design, analog and digital circuitry and microcontrollers for control. The candidate should be confident and capable of working on his / her own but also able to interact with other team members and provide oral and written reports. Experience with developing multiple simultaneous hardware and firmware products, product test requirements, FCC, UL, and EMI certification, documentation and working with manufacturing team to develop and manufacture products is necessary. This is a hands-on position for product development with substantial growth opportunities. Design of power, analog, and digital circuits Design of closed loop and/or PID loops for power and voltage control in power supply Testing and improvement of circuit designs Circuit layout, outsourcing for build, assembly and testing Electrical / mechanical / thermal characterization (modeling a plus) Development of BOM, costing, design specs and test results Provide oral and written reports to management and customers Actively contribute to the firmware development Familiarity with many various microcontrollers (Texas Instruments a plus) Current hands-on Engineering skills in hardware and firmware development for embedded systems Demonstrated innovation with a track record of power design background Circuit layout, build and assembly experience Flexibility to work in a small company start-up environment, and enthusiasm to handle a wide range of tasks as needed Must be local Min of 7 years of related Electrical Engineering experience BS/MS in Electrical Engineering Power supply design experience Some experience with Contract Manufacturers and Mobile devices Experience with Electromagnetic Emission and other Regulatory standards ');";
